        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>flatcars [300212828], freight cars by form [300228357], freight cars [300212993], railroad cars [300233722], rail guideway vehicles [300228410], guideway vehicles [300212494], land vehicles by form [300215717], land vehicles [300212968], vehicles (transportation) [300219258], Transportation Vehicles (hierarchy name) [300042929], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Flatcars with large depressed central sections designed primarily to accommodate intermodal containers; used since the mid-20th century. For flatcars with smaller depressed central portions for oversized loads, in use since the early 20th century, use "depressed center flatcars."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Platte goederenwagons met een groot dieper deel in het midden die vooral zijn ontworpen voor intermodale containers; in gebruik sinds halverwege de 20e eeuw. Gebruik 'depressed center flatcars' voor platte goederenwagons met kleinere diepere delen in het midden voor zeer grote vrachten, die in gebruik zijn sinds het begin van de 20e eeuw.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Flachwagen mit großem tiefer gelegten mittleren Bereich, hauptsächlich für die Unterbringung von genormten Containern für den kombinierten Verkehr entworfen; seit Mitte des 20. Jahrhunderts im Einsatz. Für den Flachwagen mit einem kleineren tiefer gelegten Mittelbereich für übergroße Ladung und seit Anfang des 20. Jahrhunderts im Einsatz, siehe "Tiefladegüterwagen".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
